! Enjoying Parsing

John Brant (brant@refactoryworkers.com)

""Abstract:"" Parsers are perceived to be difficult to develop. To dispel this myth we show how the development environment can make building and handling parsers enjoyable. The talk shows examples of SmaCC development.


""Bio:"" 
John has been building program analysis and transformation tools for over 25 years. He is the co-author of the Smalltalk Refactoring Browser, the first widely-used refactoring environment for any computer language. He is also the co-author of SmaCC, a parser generator for Smalltalk. Recently, he has been using SmaCC to analyze, refactor, and migrate programs written in many different languages.
